latestIgtvVideos.caption:
in a world full of 30s videos here’s a 2:16 min gratitude note. 

Everytime i hit a milestone, i feel it’s not a big deal… i shouldn’t be overexcited. That feeling is followed by a sudden rush of gratitude out of nowhere making me want to appreciate and share gratitude to my favourite people, my peach gang & myself.

That’s all this is, a thank you note & a reminder for me to celebrate big or small events with the same over-excitement everytime. 

Special mention to my A-team: @tarkeshwar_4010 @ayushguha & @shubhi_raina for being the fuel to my art ❤️ max love to you guys. 

Alright, peach out 🍑

15th june 2019, i moved to delhi from panchkula, aimless and super nervous. I quit a safe job to be a ‘talent’ for @mensxpofficial. @santu.misra, in all his wisdom: hired me even after i gave a terrible audition. By terrible i mean: i couldn’t even speak. Till date i have no idea why he hired me.

It was a 3 month probational gig with no certainty of the future. By that time i had already been making videos for 4 years, it was worth a shot yk? the worst that would happen is that I would suck and come back home and will try to pick up from where i left off. I never planned what would happen but i am so glad i did not. 

20th june 2022, I’m on the freaking cover of @mensxpofficial. Damn, i should make a youtube video about this.

thank you for everything, always. I couldn’t have asked for a better community 🤍

As humans, we are always taught to act outward. We’re taught to pursue the best; the best college, the best people, the best opportunities, to keep chasing the most thrilling experiences & my favourite ‘Never Settle’. While there is nothing wrong with striving for excellence, i really do wish someone told me how important it is to take time to act inward, to sit still and listen to yourself like you are someone you care for, to write your true feelings on a piece of paper & to have long conversations without a reason.

For me, to be able to hear yourself is one of the greatest forms of self care, to witness your thoughts with sole purpose of acknowledging them is then nothing short of a superpower. When I look back, I’ve found most answers about my life & the direction I want it to take in powerful question. Questions that came up in conversations with my friends, in books or even randomly on the internet. These powerful questions have always acted as a guiding light for me which is why I, along-with my childhood best friend @jatinjunejaa, have curated this journal for you.
